INSERT INTO `passages` (`id`, `passage_title`, `passage_text`, `exercise_id`, `createdby`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, 'passage1', 'sasas', 93, 15, '2018-06-06 17:49:11', '2018-06-06 09:49:11'),
(2, 'test6-2(ex12-14)', 'In 1919, H. S. reed and R. H. Holland published a paper on the growth of sunflowers. Included in the paper were the table and graph above, which show the height h, in centimeters, of a sunflower t days after the sunflower begins to grow.', 12, 17, '2018-06-10 21:05:05', '2018-06-10 13:05:05'),
(3, 'test6-2(ex17-19)', 'When designing a stairway, an architect can use the riser-read formula 2h + d = 25, where is the riser height, in inches, and d is the tread depth, in inches. For any given stairway, the riser heights are the same and the tread depths. Are the same for all steps in that stairway.\r\nThe number of steps in a stairway is the number of its risers, for example, there are 5 steps in the stairway in the figure above. The total rise of stairway in the figure above. The total rise of a stairway is the sum of the riser heights as shown in the figure.', 12, 17, '2018-06-11 01:44:43', '2018-06-10 17:45:22'),
(4, 'test7-2(ex7-8)', 'The scatterplot above shows the densities of 7 planetoids, in grams per cubic centimeter, with respect to their average distances from the sun in astronomical units (AU). The line of best fit is also shown.', 13, 17, '2018-06-20 21:43:15', '2018-06-20 13:43:41'),
(5, 'test7-2(ex19-20)', 'The formula above are used in medicine to estimate the body surface area. A, in square meters, of infants and children whose weight w ranges between 3 and 30 kilograms and whose height h is measured in centimeters.', 13, 17, '2018-06-20 22:40:35', '2018-06-20 14:40:35'),
(6, 'test7-2(ex37-38)', 'The same 20 contestants, on each of 3 days, answered 5 questions in order to win a prize. Each contestant received 1 point for each correct answer. The number of contestant receiving a given score on each day is shown in the table above.', 13, 17, '2018-06-21 00:15:57', '2018-06-20 16:15:57'),
