\';\">Ms. Simon drives her car from her home to her workplace every workday morning. The table above shows the distance, in miles, and her average driving speed, in miles per hour (mph), when there is no traffic delay, for each segment of her drive.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\';\"><br /><br />One morning, Ms. Simon drive directly from her home to her workplace in 24 minutes. What was her average speed, in miles per hour, during her drive that morning?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\';\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 11, 'medium', 'The correct answer is 87/2, 43.5, 43, or 44. The distance from\r\nMs. Simon\'s home to her workplace is 0.6 + 15.4 + 1.4 = 17.4 miles,\r\nMs. Simon took 24 minutes to drive this distance. Since there are\r\n60 minutes in one hour, her average speed, in miles per hour, for this trip is 17.4/24 x 60 = 43.5 miles per hour. Based on the directions, 87/2  or 43.5 can be gridded as the correct answer. Numbers 43 and 44 are additional correct answers because the precision of the measurements provided does not support an answer with three significant digits.', '2018-06-03 16:48:42', '2018-06-03 16:49:09'),
