ccording to the table, the value of y increases by 14/4=7/2 every time the value of x increases by 1. It follows that the simplest equation relating y to x is linear and of the form y = 7/2x+ b for some constant b. Furthermore, the ordered pair (1, 11/4) from the table must satisfy this equation. Substituting 1 for x and 11/4 for y in the equation y = 7/2x + b gives 11/4 = 7/2(1) + b. Solving this equation for b gives b = -3/4. Therefore, the equation in choice D correctly relates y to x.\r\nChoices A and B are incorrect. The relationship between x and y cannot be exponential because the differences, not the ratios, of y-values are the same every time the x-values change by the same amount. Choice C is incorrect because the ordered pair (2, 25/4) is not a solution to the equation y = 3/4x + 2. Substituting 2 for x and 25/4 for y in this equation gives 25/4= 3/2 + 2, which is false.', '2018-06-10 21:50:32', '2018-06-10 21:50:32');
