(1242, '<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Men</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Women</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Total</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Chocolate</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">74</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">63</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">137</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Vanilla</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">68</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">22</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">90</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Strawberry</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">17</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">39</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">56</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Cookie Dough</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">51</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">87</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">138</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Mint Chip</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">65</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">14</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">79</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Total</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">275</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">225</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">500</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The table above shows the results of a random survery of 500 men and women.Each individual chose a flavor of ice cream that was hit or her favorite.</p>\r\n<p>Approximately what percent of the men chose mint chip as their favorite ice cream flavor?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 125, 0, 96, 'easy', 'Percent is defined as (part/whole)*100.On the chart , the number of men who chose mint chip is 65,so that\'s the part.The whole is the total number of men,which is 275.So the percent is (65/275)*100=23,6%.This is approximately 25%,so the answer is (A).Once you get the numbers ,you can also estimate.Definitely less than half the men chose mint chip,so only (A) would work.', '2018-07-02 21:52:26', '2018-07-04 19:40:08'),
(1243, '<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Men</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Women</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Total</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Chocolate</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">74</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">63</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">137</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Vanilla</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">68</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">22</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">90</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Strawberry</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">17</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">39</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">56</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Cookie Dough</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">51</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">87</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">138</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Mint Chip</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">65</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">14</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">79</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">Total</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">275</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">225</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center;\">500</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The table above shows the results of a random survery of 500 men and women.Each individual chose a flavor of ice cream that was hit or her favorite.</p>\r\n<p>If a woman is chosen at random,what is the probability that her favorite ice cream flavor is strawberry?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 129, 0, 96, 'easy', 'Probability is defined as (what you want / total ) , and in this case,you want the number of women who prefer strawberry out of the number of all the women polled.So the probability is 39/225.Some questions will stop there and leave the probability as a fraction, but the answers here are decimals.Divide 39 by 225 to get about 0,17 , which is (D).', '2018-07-02 21:54:19', '2018-07-04 19:45:08'),
(1244, '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;Bcateria Reproduction</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Time</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">(in seconds)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">t</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Population</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">(in thousands)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">p</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">2</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">6</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">3</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">18</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">4</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: center;\">54</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The table above shows the population growth of a certain bacteria over four seconds.Which one of the following equations shows the one of the relationship between t and p, according to the table ?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 118, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Don\'t try to figure this one but by deriving an equation .Plug In by testing the numbers in the table against the functions in the answer choices.Plug in t=1 and p=2 .Choice (A) is 2=3(1).This is incorrect ,so eliminate (A).Choice (B) is 2= 2(1)^2 .This is correct, so keep (B).Choice (C) is 2=2*3^1.This is incorrect,so eliminate (C).Choice (D) is 2=2 * 3(1-1).This is correct ,so keep (D).Now plug t=2 and p=6 into the remaining choices.Choice (B) is 6=2(2)^2 .This is incorrect ,so eliminate (B).Choice (D) is 6=2* 3^(2-1).This is correct and is the only remaining choice,so the answer is (D).', '2018-07-04 19:57:40', '2018-07-04 19:57:40'),
(1245, '<p>&nbsp; A coffee distributor randomly polled 200 employee from each of two companies and asked each employee how many cups of coffee he or she drinks per day.The data is shown in the table below.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Employee Coffee Survey</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 47.8724%;\">Number of cups of coffee</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 7.36407%;\">0</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.6667%;\">1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 9.84852%;\">2</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9849%;\">3</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 29.1667%;\">4</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 47.8724%;\">Company X</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 7.36407%;\">5</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.6667%;\">25</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 9.84852%;\">30</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9849%;\">40</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 29.1667%;\">100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 47.8724%;\">Company Y</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 7.36407%;\">20</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.6667%;\">25</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 9.84852%;\">35</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9849%;\">45</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 29.1667%;\">75</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>There are 4,000 employees at Company X and 3,000 employees at Company Y.</p>\r\n<p>Of the employees polled at Company X,approximately what is the average number of cups of coffee consumed per employee on a given day?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 123, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Average is defined as total/#of things . There are 200 employees at Company X,so that\'s the number of things.The total is a bit harder to get from the chart.You need to find all the cups of coffee consumed by these 200 employees.Some people drank 0 cups,so you don\'t need to worry about that.The chart says that 25 people drank 1 cup each ,for 25 cups,and 30 people drank 2 cups each,for 60 more cups.There were 40 employees who drank 3 cups each,adding 120 cups,and 100 people drank 4 cups each,adding 400 more cups to the total.Add up all the cups to get 25+60+120+400=605 total cups of coffee.Plug the numbers into the average formula to get 605/200 = 3.025.This is approximately 3,so the answer is (C).', '2018-07-05 01:31:46', '2018-07-05 01:41:47'),
(1246, '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;A coffee distributor randomly polled 200 employee from each of two companies and asked each employee how many cups of coffee he or she drinks per day.The data is shown in the table below.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Employee Coffee Survey</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 44.7991%;\">Number of Cups of Coffee</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 5.43736%;\">0</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.5934%;\">1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\">2</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 9.5745%;\">3</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 23.7589%;\">4</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 44.7991%;\">Company X</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 5.43736%;\">5</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.5934%;\">25</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\">30</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 9.5745%;\">40</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 23.7589%;\">100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 44.7991%;\">Company Y</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 5.43736%;\">20</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.5934%;\">25</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\">35</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 9.5745%;\">45</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 23.7589%;\">75</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>There are 4,000 employees at Company X and 3,000 employees at Company Y.</p>\r\n<p>Based on the poll , the number of employees at Company Y who drank 0 cups of coffee was what percent greater than the number of employees at Company X who drank 0 cups of coffee?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 126, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Percent change is defined as (difference/original ) * 10 .The chart says that 5 employees at Company X and 20 employees at Company Y drank 0 cups of coffee.The difference is 20-5 = 15.The original is the number of employees from Company X who drank 0 cups.You can tell this because it asks for the \"percent greater than,\" which means that the original must be the smaller one.Therefore,the percent increase in (15\\5)*100 = 300%,which is (C).', '2018-07-05 01:48:45', '2018-07-05 01:53:34'),
(1247, '<p>&nbsp;A coffee distributor randomly polled 200 employee from each of two companies and asked each employee how many cups of coffee he or she drinks per day.The data is shown in the table below.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Employee Coffee Survey</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50.4728%;\">Number of Cups of Coffee</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 8.03783%;\">0</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9929%;\">1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\">2</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.7022%;\">3</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 21.6312%;\">4</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50.4728%;\">Company X</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 8.03783%;\">5</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9929%;\">25</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\">30</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.7022%;\">40</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 21.6312%;\">100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 50.4728%;\">Company Y</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 8.03783%;\">20</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10.9929%;\">25</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 16.6667%;\">35</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.7022%;\">45</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 21.6312%;\">75</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There are 4,000 employees at Company X and 3,000 employees at Company Y.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What is the difference between the expected total number of employees who drink 1 cup of coffee at Company X and the expected total number of employees who drink 1 cup of coffee at Company Y?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 126, 0, 96, 'medium', 'In order to extrapolate poll results to a larger population.Find the percent that fit the requirement in the poll and apply it to the general population.In this case,both companies had 25 employees out of the 200 polled that drank 1 cup of coffee.Therefore, (25/100)*100= 12,5% of the employees a both companies can be expected to drink one cup of coffee per day.At company X,there are 4,000 employees,and 12,5% of 4,000=500.At company Y,there are 3000 employees,and 12,5% of 3,000=375.The difference is 500-375=125,which is (C)', '2018-07-05 02:02:06', '2018-07-05 02:02:06'),
(1248, '<p>&nbsp;The scatterplot above shows the daily profit made by a school store from selling sweatshirts and the average dailt temperature for several days in the year 2004.</p>\r\n<p>The line of best fit is also shown and has equation<img title=\"y=-4.1x+446\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?y=-4.1x+446\" />&nbsp;.Which of the following best explains how the number -4.1 in the equation relates to the scatterplot?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 126, 0, 96, 'hard', 'On tricky questions, look for opportunities to use POE.As the temperature increase, the profits of the store decrease.Look for any answer choices that say otherwise and eliminate them.Both (B) and (D) say that profits will increase with an increase in temperature,so those are incorrect.Test out the remaining answer choices by plugging in some numbers into the equation for the line of best fit.Since this is in the No Calculator section,pick easy numbers.Start with (A) and plug in x=0 and x=1.At x=0 , y= -4.1(0) + 446 = 446,and at x=1,y= -4.1(1)+446=441.9.The difference between these values is 446-441.9 = 4.1 , so  (A) is true.There is no need to check out (C):(A) is the correct answer.', '2018-07-05 20:43:09', '2018-07-05 20:43:09'),
(1249, '<p>&nbsp;In a given school week,the average daily temperature is&nbsp;<img title=\"20^{\\circ}F\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?20^{\\circ}F\" />&nbsp;on Monday,Tuesday,and Wednesday and&nbsp;<img title=\"30^{\\circ}F\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?30^{\\circ}F\" />&nbsp;on Thursday and Friday.Based on the line of best fit,what was the school store\'s approximate profit during this school week?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 121, 0, 96, 'hard', 'You could take these values and plug them into the formula to get an exact answer,but that\'s a lot of work ,especially without the use of a calculator.Instead ,use the line of best fit to estimate the profit at these temperatures.Since the answers are spread apart and you are only asked for the \"approximate profit,\" this will get you close enough.When the temperature is 20F, the line of best fit predicts a profit of about $360.Use your scantron sheet as a straightedge if you have a hard time reading the graph.There are three days is approximately $360 x 3 = $1,080.For the two days with a temperature of 30 , the profit is about $325 , so the store  earns $325 x 2 = $650 in those two days.In total,the store earns about $1,080+ $650 = $1,730 for the week.This is closet to (D), so that\'s the answer.', '2018-07-05 21:09:26', '2018-07-05 21:09:26'),
(1250, '<p>&nbsp;If&nbsp;<img title=\"t^2 = -8\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?t^2&amp;space;=&amp;space;-8\" />&nbsp;,what is the value of&nbsp;<img title=\"t^2\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?t^2\" />&nbsp;?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 127, 0, 96, 'easy', 'Take the cube root of both sides to get t= -2 , and t^2 = (-2)^2 = 4.', '2018-07-05 21:20:32', '2018-07-05 21:20:32'),
(1251, '<p>&nbsp;If 60=(7+8)(x-2) , what is the value of x?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'easy', 'Plug in the answers.Try (B) first: (15)(9-2)=(15)(7)=105.It should equal 60 ,so you need a much smaller number.Try (D):(15)(6-2)=(15)(4)=60.It works.Or you could solve the equation algebraically:\r\n                 60=15(x-2)\r\n                 60=15x-30\r\n                  90=15x\r\n                 6=x', '2018-07-05 23:04:43', '2018-07-05 23:04:43'),
(1252, '<p>&nbsp;If&nbsp;<img title=\"4x-2y=10\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?4x-2y=10\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;<img title=\"7x+2y=23\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?7x+2y=23\" />&nbsp;,what is the value of x ?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 129, 0, 96, 'easy', 'Stock \'em and add:\r\n                           4x-2=10\r\n                          7x+2y=23\r\n                    ------------------------------\r\n                       11 x = 33\r\n                      x=3', '2018-07-05 23:10:09', '2018-07-05 23:10:09'),
(1253, '<p>&nbsp;Which of the following equations is equal to 6y+6x=66 ?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 125, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Try reducing the equation in the question first,by dividing the whole thing by 6.That leaves you with x+y=11.That\'s the same as (B),if you just move the x to the other side.', '2018-07-05 23:25:49', '2018-07-05 23:39:29'),
(1254, '<p>&nbsp;For their science homework ,Brenda and Dylan calculated the volume of air that filled a spherical basketball.If the diameter of the basketball was 6,what was the volume of the air inside the basketball,to the nearest integer?<br /><br /></p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Don\'t worry---you weren\'t supposed to know this formula .It\'s provided at the start of each math section,so don\'t get freaked out .Just use the information in the question to solve for V,using your calculator .If the diameter of the basketball was 6,the radius was 3:\r\nV=(4/3) * pi * r^3 , so V=(4/3)* pi * 27= 36 pi = 113\r\nYou may see some totally unfamiliar formula on the test --- physics, for instance---but you don\'t have to understand the formula or know anything about it .All you have to do is substitute in any value they give you and solve for the variable they ask for.', '2018-07-05 23:57:05', '2018-07-05 23:57:05'),
(1255, '<p>&nbsp;Which of the following is equivalent to&nbsp;<img title=\"\\frac{\\sqrt{a}\\times \\sqrt{b}}{3\\sqrt{a}-2\\sqrt{a}}\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\\frac{\\sqrt{a}\\times&amp;space;\\sqrt{b}}{3\\sqrt{a}-2\\sqrt{a}}\" />&nbsp;?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 126, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Remember that you can multiply or divide what\'s under a square root sign and add or subtract when what\'s under the square root sign is the same.Begin by simplifying the denominator.\r\n(square a * square b )/ (3square a - 2square a) = (square a * square b)/square a = square b.', '2018-07-06 00:03:51', '2018-07-06 00:03:51'),
(1256, '<p>&nbsp;On a certain test,Radeesh earned 2 points for every correct answer and lost 1 point for every incorrect answer.If he answered all 30 questions on the test and received a score of 51,how many questions did Radeesh answer incorrectly?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 113, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Plug in the answers.If Radeesh got 2 points for every right answer,and the test had 30 questions,the top score was 60.If he got a 51,he did pretty well,so start with (A).(Remember,the answer choices represent the number of questions he answered incorrcetly.)If he missed 3,then he got 27 right. 27 x 2 = 54.Subtract 3 for 3 wrong answers, and you get 51.\r\n[Don\'t worry if you didn\'t see which answer to start with.If you started with (C),it gave you way too many wrong answers, didn\'t it? So cross off (C) and (D) and you\'ve only got two left to cry.]', '2018-07-06 18:48:37', '2018-07-06 18:48:37'),
(1257, '<p>&nbsp;If <img title=\"\\frac{1}{2} (z-4)(z+4)=m\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\\frac{1}{2}&amp;space;(z-4)(z+4)=m\" />&nbsp;,then, in term of z,what is the value of&nbsp;<img title=\"z^{2}-16\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?z^{2}-16\" />&nbsp;?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'hard', 'The easiest way to solve this equation is to recognize that (z-4)(z+4)=(z-16)^2 .Thus, you can rewrite the initial equations as 1/2 (z-16)^2 =m.Thus ,z-16^2=2m.Otherwise,Plug In.Try z=6,which means m=10.The value of z^2 - 16 is 20 , which is twice as much as m, or 2m.', '2018-07-06 18:57:27', '2018-07-06 18:57:27'),
(1258, '<p>&nbsp;If&nbsp;<img title=\"(y+5)^{2} = 49\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?(y+5)^{2}&amp;space;=&amp;space;49\" />&nbsp;,then which one of the following could be the value of&nbsp;<img title=\"(y+3)^{2}\" src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?(y+3)^{2}\" />&nbsp;?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 118, 0, 96, 'hard', 'Since (y+5)^2 = 49, take the square root of both sides.Don\'t forget that the result could be positive or negative, so y+5 = (+ or - ) 7.Consider both cases.If y+5=7 , then y=2.In this case, (y+3)^2 = (2+3)^2 = 5^2 = 25.\r\nThis is not a choice,so consider the other case.If y+5= -7,then y=-12 .In this case, (y+3)^2 = (-12+3)^2 = (-9)^2 = 81, which is (C).', '2018-07-06 19:06:11', '2018-07-06 19:06:11'),
(1259, '<p>&nbsp;If a-b = 4 , b-6=c , c-2=d , and a+d=4, what is the value of a?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 120, 0, 96, 'hard', 'Start off by eliminating (D), as that would be too easy for  a complicated looking question toward the end.Before you start the lengthy process of substitution ,try stack-and-add.You need to bring all of the variables to the left and all of the numbers to the right,so your stack will look like this:\r\n                                a-b=4\r\n                                b-c=6\r\n                                c-d=2\r\n                                a+d=4\r\nAdd everything up.It turns out that b,c and d disappear, leaving 2a=16, or a=8.', '2018-07-06 19:15:44', '2018-07-06 19:15:44'),
(1260, '<p>&nbsp;In the figure above,what is the value of 3a-a?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 125, 0, 96, 'easy', 'A triangle has 180. So 90+35+a=180, and a=55.Plug that into the equation and get 3(55)-55=110.', '2018-07-07 19:17:13', '2018-07-07 19:17:13'),
(1261, '<p>&nbsp;In the figure above,what is the value of b?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 127, 0, 96, 'easy', '5b and b lie on a straight line,so 5b+b=180 and b=30.', '2018-07-07 19:23:53', '2018-07-07 19:23:53'),
(1262, '<p>&nbsp;In the xy-plane above ,what is the value of the x-coordinate of point A minus the y-coordinate of Point B?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'easy', 'The x-coordinate of Point A is 3,and the y-coordinate of Point B is -2.\r\nSo 3-(-2)=5.', '2018-07-07 19:28:16', '2018-07-07 19:28:16'),
(1263, '<p>&nbsp;Point P is the center of the circle shown above,which has a radius of 4.Which of the following points lies on circle P?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'medium', 'The coordinates are given ,so don\'t worry about trying to make an equation or manipulating the radius or anything like that.Just plot the points and see which one falls on the circle.Remember that on the circle means on the circumference rather than inside the circumference.Choices (A) ,(B) and (D) are all inside the circle.Only (C) is on the circumference.', '2018-07-07 19:38:13', '2018-07-07 19:38:13'),
(1264, '<p>&nbsp;In the rectangle above,what is the value of p+q-r ?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 122, 0, 96, 'medium', 'As always, mark whatever info you can on your diagram: r=90 , and the angle on the bottom right is also 90, because this is a rectangle . p+q = 90,because they are the two remaining angles in a right triangle.\r\nThat means p+q-r = 90-90 = 0.', '2018-07-07 19:47:04', '2018-07-07 19:47:04'),
(1265, '<p>&nbsp;In the figure above, what is the value of p+q ?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Again , mark info on the diagram.The unmarked angle of the triangle is 50 because l1 , and l2 are parallel, and the unmarked angle and the 50 angle are both small, so 50+p+q=180 and p+q= 130. (You can\'t figure out what p and q are individually , but the question doesn\'t ask you to anyway.)', '2018-07-07 19:53:04', '2018-07-07 19:53:04'),
(1266, '<p>&nbsp;The figure above is formed by a triangle overlapping a rectangle.What is the value of a+b ?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 126, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Estimate first. The angle marked a is greater than 90, and you are adding b to it .Therefore, (A) is too small .Choice (D) looks too big, since that would be the sum of two obtuse angles,and b is less than 90.Now only (B) and (C) are left.To figure out the sum of the angles , ignore the triangle and look at the quadrilateral in the bottom half of the rectangle.The angles are a+b+90+90.Since a quadrilateral has 360 , a+b=180.', '2018-07-07 20:03:02', '2018-07-07 20:03:02'),
(1267, '<p>&nbsp;Which of the following statements must be true?</p>\r\n<p>1. a+b &lt;180</p>\r\n<p>2. a+d =180</p>\r\n<p>3. a+d &gt;180</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 125, 0, 96, 'hard', 'It\'s important to realize what you don\'t know:Are any of these lines parallel? You don\'t know .So you can\'t draw any conclusions at all other than the rule that a line contains 180.Keep this simple and imagine that all the intersecting lines are perpendicular.In this case,a+b=180, so 1. is false.Also , a+d=180, so 2. is true but 3. is false.Eliminate any choice that includes 1. or 3. : Choices (C) and (D) are out.Because the lines do not have to be parallel, there is no necessary relation ship between a and d.It could be 90 and d could be 60.In this case, a+d=150, so 2. false.Eliminate (B).Only (A) remains.', '2018-07-07 20:15:58', '2018-07-07 20:15:58'),
(1268, '<p>&nbsp;The tick marks on the number line above are equally spaced.If 2 is halfway between b and c,and the value of c-a is 10, what is the value of b?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 125, 0, 96, 'hard', 'The best way to approach this question is to plug In the answers.Try (B) and suppose b is -2.Because the midpoint between b and c is 2,you can see that each tick mark represents a value of 2 more than the previous tick mark.Thus , a is -4 and c is 6.Now , you have to check this against the remaining information in the question.So c-a must be 10.Is it? Yes , so (B) is the answer!', '2018-07-07 20:22:31', '2018-07-07 20:22:31'),
(1269, '<p>&nbsp;What is the total number of degrees of the marked angles?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'hard', 'Estimate first and see what you can cross out.Since you have two angles that are bigger than 90 and one angle that\'s bigger than 180, you should be able at least to cross out (A) and (B).To figure out the exact number of degrees, divide the figure into three triangles:\r\nThe total degrees will be 180 x 3 = 540. Alternatively , know that each side added to a figure adds 180. A three- sided figure (i.e., a triangle) has 180 , so a four -sided figure has 360 , and a five-sided figure has 540.', '2018-07-07 20:29:55', '2018-07-07 20:29:55'),
(1270, '<p>&nbsp;If the area of the triangle above is 6, what is its perimeter?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 124, 0, 96, 'easy', 'There are several ways to get this question: You could recognize that it\'s a Pythagorean triple (3:4:5) , which would give you the length of the unmarked leg.Or you could set up the following equation:\r\n                                 a = (1/2) bh\r\n(1/2)b(4)=6 so 2b=6 and b=3.All that did was substitute the height and the area, both of which are given in the problem, into the formula for the area of a triangle .Either way , the perimeter is the sum of the sides, which is 3+4+5 = 12.', '2018-07-07 20:37:54', '2018-07-07 20:37:54'),
(1271, '<p>&nbsp;If x=3 , what is the area of the triangle above?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 121, 0, 96, 'easy', 'f x=3 , then the base of the triangle is 6 and the height is 15.That would mean the area is (1/2)(6)(15)=45', '2018-07-07 20:43:10', '2018-07-07 20:43:10'),
(1272, '<p>&nbsp;If equilateral triangle ABC is cut by three lines, as shown to form four equilateral triangles of equal area, what is the length of side of one of the smaller triangles?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 120, 0, 96, 'easy', 'Because all the small triangles and the big triangle are equilateral , each vertex of the small triangles bisects a side of the big triangle ,which means that each side is 6. (Don\'t forget to estimate.)', '2018-07-07 20:49:02', '2018-07-07 20:49:02'),
(1273, '<p>&nbsp;What is the value of p in the figure above?</p>', NULL, 'richtext', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 122, 0, 96, 'medium', 'Start with the triangle to the right of the height line .As the height forms an angle of 90 and the given angle is 20, the third angle is 70 (180-170).Thus, 2q=70 , and q=35.Now go to the triangle to the left of the height line.As the height forms an angle  of 90 and q is 35, p is 55.', '2018-07-07 21:02:43', '2018-07-07 21:02:43'),
